cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless sensor networks and their deployment. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper models the deployment problem as a quantization problem with distortion defined as the total power consumption of the network. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a heterogeneous two-tier Lloyd algorithm to optimize the node deployment. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possible category as the paper deals with the deployment of multiple heterogeneous nodes in a network. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper proposes a cell partitioning algorithm for the network.
